External services / processes used at runtime (not bundled — invoked via
separate processes / HTTP / WebRTC):

- Claude Code CLI / claude-agent-sdk    MIT          (Anthropic)
- Sunshine                              GPL-3.0      (LizardByte)
- moonlight-web-stream                  GPL-3.0      (MrCreativ3001)
- Tailscale (client)                    BSD-3-Clause (Tailscale Inc.)

The GPL components above are not statically linked or bundled into this
repository. They are accessed as external processes via HTTP / WebRTC, so
the GPL copyleft does not propagate (FSF GPL FAQ: process separation is
not typically a derivative work).

Specifically for moonlight-web-stream: the PWA frontend embeds its UI via
an <iframe src="/moonlight/"> after Tailscale Serve reverse-proxies the
moonlight-web-stream's own web server (= a separate process the user
builds + runs themselves; this repo ships neither source nor binaries of
it). iframe embedding creates a separate document context and qualifies
as aggregation rather than a derivative work under the GPL.
